data.sampled:
The Ebola virus disease (EVD) is a severe and often fatal illness that can occur in people and animals. There are currently several treatment options available for individuals who contract EVD:

* Vaccination: Vaccines have been developed to provide protection against EVD. These vaccines work by stimulating the body's immune system to produce antibodies against the virus.
* Antiviral medications: A few antiviral medications have shown promise in treating EVD. They work by targeting the virus directly and preventing it from replicating.
* Supportive care: This type of care focuses on providing support to patients while their bodies fight off the virus. It may include hydration, electrolyte replacement, blood transfusions, oxygen therapy, and other interventions to manage symptoms such as fever and pain.

It is important for those who suspect they may have been exposed to EVD to seek medical attention immediately. Early diagnosis and prompt treatment can improve chances of recovery.
